26/11/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Miodrag Zivkovic was re-elected as leader of the opposition Liberal Party (LP) at the party congress in Podgorica on Saturday (November 25th). The delegates also elected five party deputy chairpersons and adopted a procedural resolution, regarding the activities of municipal branches. This was the party's first regular convention since its establishment in 2004. (Pobjeda, Vijesti - 26/11/06)
